Distinguish ClamAV "Heuristics.Limits.Exceeded.*" from real virus hits.

ClamAV reports scan-limit overruns (MaxScanSize, MaxFileSize, MaxRecursion,
MaxFiles, MaxEmbeddedPE, etc.) through the same "stream: <name> FOUND"
channel as actual virus detections. The current regex matches both, so a
file that is merely too large or too complex to fully scan is reported to
the user as "A virus has been detected. The file will be deleted." which is
a false positive.

This patch:
  - Adds a new result constant Scanner::FILE_EXCEEDS_SCAN_LIMITS.
  - Detects the "Heuristics.Limits.Exceeded.*" prefix in DaemonTCPIP,
    DaemonUnixSocket, and Executable backends and remaps to the new state.
  - Logs the event as a warning (not an error) and surfaces a clear,
    actionable message to the end user instead of the misleading
    "virus detected" text.
  - Honours the existing outage_action setting: when the site is configured
    to allow unchecked uploads, limit-exceeded files are also allowed
    through (consistent with the FILE_IS_UNCHECKED branch).

Issue ref: DP-45788 — large but clean PDFs rejected as "virus detected"
on Acquia where ClamAV MaxScanSize is below the post-decompression scan
size of the document.

diff --git a/src/Scanner.php b/src/Scanner.php
--- a/src/Scanner.php
+++ b/src/Scanner.php
@@ -19,6 +19,11 @@ class Scanner {
   const FILE_IS_UNCHECKED = -1;
   const FILE_IS_CLEAN     = 0;
   const FILE_IS_INFECTED  = 1;
+  // The file exceeded one of ClamAV's scan limits (e.g. MaxScanSize,
+  // MaxFileSize, MaxRecursion, MaxFiles) and was not fully scanned. This is
+  // distinct from FILE_IS_INFECTED because no actual virus signature was
+  // matched; the scanner simply gave up before finishing.
+  const FILE_EXCEEDS_SCAN_LIMITS = 2;

   // Constants defining whether a specific file should be scanned.
   const FILE_IS_SCANNABLE     = TRUE;
@@ -213,6 +218,12 @@ class Scanner {
           \Drupal::logger('Clam AV')->info($message, $replacements);
         }
         break;
+
+      // Log files that exceeded ClamAV scan limits.
+      case self::FILE_EXCEEDS_SCAN_LIMITS:
+        $message = 'Uploaded file %filename exceeded ClamAV scan limits (%virusname) and was not fully scanned.' . $debug_output;
+        \Drupal::logger('Clam AV')->warning($message, $replacements);
+        break;
     }
     return $result;
   }
